All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
Character
This class defines the basic attributes of a Character on screen.
EndLoseScreen
This class holds everything that is shown on the "Game Over" screen.
EndWinScreen
This class holds everything that is shown on the "You Win" screen.
Enemy
This class inherits the Character class and adds attributes specific to the Enemy.
Frame
This class creates the initial start screen that the user sees.
GameTime
This class holds the in game timer that is displayed at the left corner of the game screen.
Graphic
The purpose of this class holds all of the game logic for the graphic interface of the game.
Hero
This class inherits the Character class and adds attributes specific to the Hero.
ImageLoader
The purpose of this class is to load in all images for the Graphics of the game.
Main
This class initializes the game frame and starts the game.
Map
The purpose of this class creates the game board on a 2-dimensional array placing the game pieces to their initial positions.
Play
This class creates the user interface of the game, meaning that every feature including the JPanels in the bottom part of the game screen is constructed here.
Start
This class holds the Start screen as it also creates the game frame for the next state when the user hits the start button on the Start screen, also includes a Quit button if the user decides the leave right away.
Util
This class handles the distance between two objects.
